  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "Create or consolidate design tokens for colors, spacing, typography, radius, borders, elevation, semantic states, and map-layer states without adding unapproved production dependencies.",
    "Create centralized asset replacement slots or an equivalent registry for frames, icons, map fills/strokes, route styles, settlement markers, portraits, alerts, settings/language, and tooltips.",
    "Clearly distinguish neutral placeholders from final production art; culture-specific symbols, portraits, scripts, flags, religious imagery, clothing, architecture, music, and ritual motifs remain review-gated.",
    "Components must not hard-code final asset paths, culture-specific imagery, or scattered visual constants that prevent later reviewed art replacement.",
    "Storybook or equivalent evidence must show core token states, English and Simplified Chinese layout stress, enabled/disabled/warning/success/danger states, and debug-on/off distinction.",
    "No map art, token, slot, or placeholder becomes authoritative simulation, historical, content, save, or command state."
  ],
